  ;; ============================================================
  ;; Schematic Sheet Instances
  ;; ============================================================

  ;; Top-level connections are documented in phase2 netlists.
  ;; This schematic symbol block defines all major components and
  ;; their pin-level interfaces. In a full KiCad project, hierarchical
  ;; sheets would be used for:
  ;;   Sheet 1: Power supply (PMIC, USB PD, LDOs)
  ;;   Sheet 2: Analog front-end (attenuators, drivers, ADCs)
  ;;   Sheet 3: Digital front-end (comparators, threshold DAC)
  ;;   Sheet 4: FPGA + DDR3L
  ;;   Sheet 5: MCU + peripherals (STM32, SPI, I2C, UART)
  ;;   Sheet 6: USB + isolation (USB3340, ISO7740)
  ;;   Sheet 7: Wi-Fi (ESP32-C6)
  ;;   Sheet 8: Connectors (BNC, MCX, USB-C, SMA, SD)

  ;; Net connections documented in phase2:
  ;; - U1(ADC1_CLK_P) → U3(CLKP) via LVDS pair
  ;; - U1(ULPI_DATA0..7) → U10(DATA0..7) via ULPI bus
  ;; - U1(DDR3_*) → U9(*) via DDR3L bus
  ;; - U2(PB6/PB7) → U11(SCL/SDA) via I2C1
  ;; - U2(PB8/PB9) → U12(SCL/SDA) via I2C2
  ;; - U2(PA4..PA7) → U16(CS_N/CLK/MISO/MOSI) via SPI1
  ;; - U2(PB2..PB5) → U15(SCL/SDA/SCK/MOSI) via SPI2 (DAC threshold)
  ;; - U2(PB13..PB15/PC6) → U1(MCU_SPI_*) via SPI4 (FPGA config)
  ;; - U14(OUT_A1) → U10(USB_DP) via isolated USB
  ;; - U14(OUT_A2) → U10(USB_DM) via isolated USB
  ;; - J1(J5) → U14(IN_A1/IN_A2) via USB-C connector + ESD

)